# Dashboard layout (locked)

## KPI grid — locked

File: `src/app/sections/kpi/kpi.component.html`

- **Never** `grid-cols-1` at any breakpoint.
- **Default:** `grid-cols-2` (2×2 on mobile/tablet).
- **Wide desktop:** `xl:grid-cols-4` (four in one row).
- Typography scale at **`xl:`**, not `md:`.

Do not edit KPI grid classes unless the user explicitly requests a KPI layout change.

## Page grid vs sections

- **Page shell only:** `@container/dashboard` on `dashboard-page`, column classes in `dashboard-layout.ts`, section hosts in `dashboard.page.html`.
- **Section templates** (bottleneck, trends, schedule, requisitions, funnel, kpi): use existing **`lg:`** stretch internally — do **not** swap to `@min-[…]/dashboard:` inside sections without explicit ask.
- **Card stretch PT** in `dashboard-layout.ts`: stays on **`lg:`**; container queries are for page-level column widths only.

## Row breakers

`DASHBOARD_SECTION_FULL_ROW` uses `@min-[43.25rem]/dashboard:basis-full` only when `main` is flex-row — never bare `basis-full` in flex-col (sets height, not width).

## Before any layout pass

Ask which tier is in scope. Do not bundle mobile order, KPI, section internals, and page grid in one diff unless the user lists all of them.
